5. ISO AND DUAL NATIVE ISO

  Panasonic S series (S1H, S5 II, S5 IIX) feature Dual Native ISO:

  S1H:
    Low Base ISO  : 640  (native analog gain)
    High Base ISO : 4000 (native analog gain with lower read noise)
    Read noise (Low): ~1.8 e-; (High): ~1.0 e-
    Full well capacity (Low): ~48,000 e-
    Dynamic range: 14+ stops (SNR=1)

  S5 II / S5 IIX:
    Low Base ISO  : 640
    High Base ISO : 4000
    Read noise (Low): ~1.6 e-; (High): ~0.9 e-
    Full well capacity (Low): ~42,000 e-

  GH6 / GH7 (Micro Four Thirds):
    Low Base ISO  : 500
    High Base ISO : 2000
    Read noise: ~1.2 e- (High)
    Dynamic range: 13+ stops

  The IDT is gain-state independent. The same inverse V-Log and matrix
  apply regardless of ISO. ISO metadata selects noise profile only.

6. METADATA HANDLING
  Panasonic MOV and RAW containers carry:
    - Log curve (V-Log or V-Log L flag)
    - ISO / Dual Native ISO state
    - White balance (Kelvin + tint)
    - Lens data (L-mount or MFT metadata)

  GIOP reads these values. If metadata is absent, the IDT defaults to
  V-Log, ISO 640 Low Gain, and Daylight.

